commitResults.messageTitle: Update AboutUs and README pages, add UI mockup and build status badge
commitResults.messageBody:
AboutUs Page:
- Updated team member details and roles
- Added profile photos for each member
- Followed specified format for photo filenames

README Page:
- Updated project details and content to match project
- Added UI mockup image as docs/images/Ui.png

Build Status Badge:
- Updated GitHub Actions build status badge link to reflect team repo's build status

Acknowledgement:
- Acknowledged original source of code

This commit reflects updates made to various pages in the project repository to match our project details and specifications.

This commit reflects changes made to the README
to update project details and information.
The README now accurately reflects our project and
its specifications.

The user stories does not align with our overall
objective of creating a mini-CRM system.

This may make the overall project very confusing
if other developers were to see the developer
guide and not see the updated user stories.

Update the user stories to match what my group
is trying to attain.

This will be more accurate to what we would like
to achieve the next few weeks, and also to meet
the requirements of this module.

No other reference.
